In this speech delivered at a private residence in Beverly Hills, California, President Joe Biden discusses various topics, including the state of the economy, the conflict with Russia over Ukraine, and the importance of the upcoming off-year election. He highlights the need to address issues like inflation and the rising cost of food, while also emphasizing the urgency of protecting women's reproductive rights and gun safety measures. President Biden expresses concern about the direction of the Republican Party, particularly its alignment with former President Donald Trump, and urges his audience to support Democratic candidates in order to prevent a setback in progress. He concludes by thanking the attendees for their support and urging them to continue their efforts.